Callistosporium is a genus of fungi in the family Tricholomataceae. The genus is widespread, and contains 13 species.


== Species ==
C. amazonicum
C. chrysophorum
C. foetens
C. galerinoides
C. heimii
C. krambrukum
C. luteo-olivaceum
C. marginatum
C. olivascens
C. palmarum
C. pinicola
C. purpureomarginatum
C. terrigenum
C. vinosobrunneum
C. xerampelinum


